This paper focuses on language analysis of public online discussions of breaking news events on social media platforms, specifically Facebook and Twitter. The paper examines how people refer to locations and how the use of contextual descriptors is associated with social and informational expectations. This work involves natural language processing and social media analysis, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), social and information networks (cs.SI), social and behavioral sciences (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
